articles.author: Tom Balmforth, Olena Harmash
articles.description: Ukraine used U.S. ATACMS missiles to strike Russian territory for the first time, Moscow said, in a major escalation on the war's 1,000th day.
articles.title: Ukraine hits Russia with US missiles for first time on war's 1,000th day

articles.author: Maya Gebeily
articles.description: Intensifying efforts for a truce in Lebanon have brought into focus the role of the country's army, which would be expected to keep the south free of Hezbollah weapons but is neither willing nor able to confront the Iran-backed group, seven sources said.
articles.title: As truce talks progress, Lebanon's army cornered by politics, funding

articles.author: Lisandra Paraguassu, Elizabeth Pineau
articles.description: As world leaders at the G20 summit in Brazil are bracing for the return of U.S. President Donald Trump to the center of global affairs, one head of state in the room has given them an early taste of a familiar, iconoclastic right-wing style.
articles.title: Argentina's Milei plays Trump stand-in at G20 summit in Rio

articles.author: Humeyra Pamuk, Simon Lewis
articles.description: Senior U.S. and Israeli officials will hold talks in early December in the first meeting of a new channel requested by Washington to raise concerns over civilian harm in Israel's war in Gaza, State Department spokesperson Matthew Miller said on Tuesday.
articles.title: US, Israeli officials will discuss civilian harm in Gaza in early December, State Department says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The funeral of former One Direction star Liam Payne, who died last month in a fall from the balcony of his Buenos Aires, is expected to take place on Wednesday, British media reported.
articles.title: Liam Payne's funeral to take place on Wednesday, British media reports

articles.author: Joey Roulette
articles.description: Elon Musk's SpaceX launched its sixth Starship test flight to space on Tuesday from Texas, eyeing an array of improvements on the rocket as U.S. President-elect Donald Trump watched in person.
articles.title: Trump, Musk watch SpaceX's Starship lift off from Texas

articles.author: Andreas Rinke, Sarah Marsh
articles.description: Pressure is piling on Germany's unpopular Chancellor Olaf Scholz to let someone else lead his Social Democrats into the upcoming snap election to give the party now languishing in third place in polls a better shot of catching up.
articles.title: Pressure grows on Germany's Scholz over bid for second term

articles.author: Simon Lewis
articles.description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken on Tuesday called Venezuela's Edmundo Gonzalez the country's "president-elect" for the first time, signaling that Washington wants to step up pressure on incumbent President Nicolas Maduro.
articles.title: Blinken calls Venezuela's opposition leader Gonzalez 'president-elect'

articles.author: Lisandra Paraguassu, Elizabeth Pineau, Andreas Rinke
articles.description: European delegates at the G20 summit in Brazil were unhappy with President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva's decision to end talks and issue the group's final statement a day early to curtail prickly discussion on the war in Ukraine, sources said.
articles.title: Lula cuts G20 discussion short on Ukraine, irking Europeans

articles.author: Kate Abnett, Gloria Dickie, Ali Kucukgocmen
articles.description: Australia and Turkey are in a standoff over which country is better suited to host United Nations climate change talks in 2026, with neither willing to give up on their bid.
articles.title: Australia, Turkey in 2026 UN climate summit hosting standoff
